 WSE</a>.</p></li><li><p>Het loopbaanattest mag maximaal 6 jaar oud zijn. </p></li><li><p>U voegt het loopbaanattest samen met het inschrijvingsattest van de opleiding toe aan de aanvraag.</p></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>","en":"<ul><li>You are an employee or temporary worker.<br />Employees in both the private and public sectors are eligible.<br />If you are in a situation of temporary unemployment, you are still under an employment contract with your employer and are eligible.</li><li>You live<ul><li>in Flanders or in the Brussels-Capital Region</li><li>in a country other than Belgium that belongs to the EU or the EEA and you work in Flanders or the Brussels-Capital Region</li><li>in Wallonia, after you have moved there from another country (other than Belgium) that belongs to the EU or the EEA <u>and</u> you work in Flanders or in the Brussels-Capital Region.</li></ul></li><li>You are following a training course at your own initiative and at your own expense.</li><li>You are:<ul><li>low- or medium-skilled (you have at most a certificate of secondary education): in that case you can use a training voucher to pay for career-oriented training as well as all training courses registered in the ‘<a href=\"http://www.vlaanderen.be/opleidingsdatabank\">Training course database of Flemish training incentives'</a>.</li><li>highly skilled (you have a graduate, bachelor’s or master’s degree): in that case you can only use a training voucher to pay for career-oriented training.</li></ul></li></ul><p> </p><h3>Which training courses?</h3><p>You can use training vouchers to pay for:</p><ul><li>a training course that is registered in the <a href=\"http://www.vlaanderen.be/opleidingsdatabank\">Training course database of Flemish training incentives</a><ul><li>only valid if you have at most a certificate of secondary education (so only for low- or medium-skilled).</li></ul></li><li>career-oriented training<ul><li>applicable to low- medium- and highly skilled</li><li>career-oriente